My husband and I really enjoyed the movie..... it did not feel like a over 2 hour movie... like the twists!
one of the best murder mystery movies out there! highly recommend

This movie was just beyond amazing. It is nothing like you predicted. It is totally a fresh new take on the whodunnit genre. The cast was incredibly fabulous. All of them were hilariously talented. The looks and feels of the film were stunning too. Rian Johnson is such genius. I've seen it twice already and I don't mind go and see it again.

I felt the movie lacked some identity, It didn't seem as though Johnson wasn't sure if he was making a comedy or a drama. The drama wasn't intense enough for the comedy to feel like breaks in the tension but the movie wasn't funny enough to be a comedy. The whodunnit aspect of the film is enjoyable, the acting is phenomenal, but the inter-family relationships were presented as interesting material to develop or expand on but that fell a little short as well. Watchable and entertaining but I left wanting more and not in the good way.
Great movie, w lots of twists & turns to find the killer.

This was a poorly written/executed movie.  You see the culprit from 500 miles away (no surprises).  The cinematography & acting were fine...honestly they had a lot of talent but not a lot to work with story-wise.  Skip this one...

Everyone is great. Chris Evans shines in a totally different role from his previous one as Captain America. He's a star! Craig is amazing too, Ana De Armas a revelation. Everyone is so awesome. Great ensemble, great actors, great writer/director who made a "must see" movie. Go see it!

I've looked forward to this movie for the last month and was so happy when it was even better than I'd expected. The cast is so well-chosen and the story is intricately written as well as not being too complex.  Overall it was a great story and a lot of fun!
